WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.520
[Amit Varma]: One of the great tragedies of life is that by the time we have lived long enough to gain

00:00:10.520 --> 00:00:13.960
[Amit Varma]: wisdom, we are not young enough to do anything with it.

00:00:13.960 --> 00:00:19.260
[Amit Varma]: This is why technology, from the Gutenberg press to your podcast app, is so marvellous.

00:00:19.260 --> 00:00:22.320
[Amit Varma]: We have access to the wisdom of others.

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:26.300
[Amit Varma]: This is also why I love these long, rambling conversations I have.

00:00:26.300 --> 00:00:30.520
[Amit Varma]: The point of the conversation is not always the subject that might have sparked it off,

00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:35.800
[Amit Varma]: but instead what you get to learn in the digressions that you take through the side roads of someone's

00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:36.800
[Amit Varma]: mind.

00:00:36.800 --> 00:00:40.920
[Amit Varma]: My guest today has been a dear friend of mine for a couple of decades, and we have spent

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:43.840
[Amit Varma]: countless hours talking about many, many things.

00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:48.600
[Amit Varma]: And yet, in this conversation, I learnt a lot about him that I hadn't known earlier.

00:00:48.600 --> 00:00:58.000
[Amit Varma]: And I also got much food for thought about the world we live in, and about my own self.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:03.480
[Unknown]: Welcome to The Seen and the Unseen, our weekly podcast on economics, politics and behavioural

00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:04.480
[Unknown]: science.

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:10.400
[Amit Varma]: Please welcome your host, Amit Verma.

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:11.800
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to The Seen and the Unseen.

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:16.400
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is Prem Panikkar, a legendary journalist who has been whipping up a storm

00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:18.680
[Amit Varma]: in the media since the late 1980s.

00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:22.560
[Amit Varma]: He's best known for his cricket writing and his ball-by-ball commentary for Rediff in

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:23.560
[Amit Varma]: the mid-1990s.

00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:26.360
[Amit Varma]: My12 have been the first blog in the world.

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:31.520
[Amit Varma]: He's also been a managing editor at Rediff and Yahoo, and has taught both journalism

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:34.280
[Amit Varma]: and writing to countless young people.

00:01:34.280 --> 00:01:38.840
[Amit Varma]: In fact, before recording this episode, I recorded a session on writing with Prem for

00:01:38.840 --> 00:01:43.080
[Amit Varma]: the YouTube channel of Windowpane, the writing community that I run.

00:01:43.080 --> 00:01:47.360
[Amit Varma]: That video will be released on Wednesday, March 24, three days from now.

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:50.680
[Amit Varma]: We spoke about sports writing and writing in general over there.

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:55.000
[Amit Varma]: But in this conversation, we didn't cover many of the subjects you'd associate with

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:56.000
[Amit Varma]: Prem.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.080
[Amit Varma]: There is little talk of cricket and writing, and we spent just the last half an hour talking

00:02:00.080 --> 00:02:01.080
[Amit Varma]: about journalism.

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:05.720
[Amit Varma]: Instead, for the first two and a half hours, we discussed broader themes around life and

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:06.720
[Amit Varma]: art.

00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:12.400
[Amit Varma]: And Prem shared a raw, intimate account of his life that I found both moving and inspiring.

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:15.240
[Amit Varma]: This conversation will always remain special for me.

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:23.160
[Amit Varma]: But before we get to it, let's take a quick commercial break.

00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:24.280
[Amit Varma]: Why should we read books?

00:02:24.280 --> 00:02:28.280
[Amit Varma]: I can think of many reasons, but one is that they teach us how to live.

00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:32.200
[Amit Varma]: To give you a sense of this, allow me to recommend an online course for you.

00:02:32.200 --> 00:02:37.840
[Amit Varma]: Head on over to the sponsors of this episode, The Great Courses Plus at thegreatcoursesplus.com

